Carol Haney https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carol_Haney 0 Carol Haney (born Carolyn Haney; August 24, 1924 – May 10, 1964) was an American dancer and actress. After assisting Gene Kelly in choreographing films, Haney won a Tony Award for her role in Broadway's The Pajama Game, while later work as a stage choreographer earned her three Tony nominations.
